23:01:13 [PROXY] body (FULL, 4764 chars): {"model":"LFM2.5-8B-A1B-Q4_K_M.gguf","messages":[{"role":"system","content":"You are a helpful assistant. Answer the user's questions using your own knowledge.\nWhen you need information from files, use the available tool. \nWhen a question includes a tool call and then another request first do tool calling and then answer.\n\nCRITICAL JSON FORMATTING RULE — every parameter MUST have a value.\n  WRONG:  {\"file_path\": \"x.txt\", \"limit\":}\n  WRONG:  {\"file_path\": \"x.txt\", \"limit\": , \"from_tail\": true}\n  WRONG:  {\"file_path\": \"x.txt\", \"limit\",}\n  RIGHT:  {\"file_path\": \"x.txt\", \"limit\": 4096}\n  RIGHT:  {\"file_path\": \"x.txt\"}    (omit the key entirely if no value)\nIf you don't know a value, OMIT the key — never emit an empty value.\n\nTool: read\nDescription: Read a file from the filesystem. Supports line-based pagination (offset/limit), byte cap (max_bytes), and tail-mode for logs. All parameters are JSON keys — use them exactly as shown.\nJSON parameters: file_path (string, required), offset (number, optional, 1-indexed line start), limit (number, optional, max lines), max_bytes (number, optional, cap bytes before line splitting, default: 2048, -1 to disable), from_tail (boolean, optional, read from end: 1 = last line)\nExamples:\n  - Read first 2048 bytes:          {\"file_path\": \"file.txt\"}\n  - Read 10 lines from offset 5:    {\"file_path\": \"file.txt\", \"offset\": 5, \"limit\": 10}\n  - Read with byte cap:             {\"file_path\": \"file.txt\", \"max_bytes\": 4096}\n  - Read last 20 lines of a log:    {\"file_path\": \"app.log\", \"from_tail\": true, \"limit\": 20}\nUsage: Always use the exact JSON key names above. Do NOT use plain-text parameter syntax.\n\nTool: get_file\nDescription: Read a text file with byte-based offset/limit for precise positioning. Unlike \"read\" which counts lines, this tool works in bytes.\nJSON parameters: file_path (string, required), offset_bytes (number, optional, default 0), limit_bytes (number, optional, max bytes to read, default 2048)\nExamples:\n  - First 2048 bytes:               {\"file_path\": \"file.txt\"}\n  - Read 4096 bytes at offset 1024: {\"file_path\": \"file.txt\", \"offset_bytes\": 1024, \"limit_bytes\": 4096}\nUsage: Increase offset_bytes to scroll forward. Use read tool for line-based navigation.\n\nTool: file_glob_search\nDescription: Search for files matching a glob pattern in a directory (non-recursive, top-level only). Returns up to 100 file names relative to the base directory.\nJSON parameters: path (string, required), exclude (string, optional, glob pattern to exclude)\nNote: This tool always searches ALL files (**). There is no extension filter.\nExamples:\n  - List all files:                 {\"path\": \".\"}\n  - Exclude .nim files:             {\"path\": \".\", \"exclude\": \"*.nim\"}\nUsage: Use this to discover files before reading them. Do NOT call read on every result — the file list is shown to the user.\nImportant: This tool searches ALL file types. Do NOT assume a specific extension.\n\n \n"},{"role":"user","content":"read \"./colosseo.txt\" max_bytes 4096"}],"stream":true,"tools":[{"type":"function","function":{"name":"read","description":"Read a file from the filesystem. Use this to read file contents.","parameters":{"type":"object","properties":{"file_path":{"type":"string","description":"Path to the file to read"},"offset":{"type":"number","description":"Line number to start reading from (1-indexed)"},"limit":{"type":"number","description":"Maximum number of lines to read"},"max_bytes":{"type":"number","description":"Maximum bytes to read before splitting into lines (default: 2048, -1 to disable)"},"from_tail":{"type":"boolean","description":"When true, offset is counted from the end of the file (1 = last line). Useful for reading log files tail-first."}},"required":["file_path"]}}},{"type":"function","function":{"name":"get_file","description":"Read a text file with byte-based offset/limit. Use this to read specific portions of a file when byte position is known.","parameters":{"type":"object","properties":{"file_path":{"type":"string","description":"Path to the file to read"},"offset_bytes":{"type":"number","description":"Byte offset to start reading from (default: 0)"},"limit_bytes":{"type":"number","description":"Maximum bytes to read (default: 2048)"}},"required":["file_path"]}}},{"type":"function","function":{"name":"file_glob_search","description":"Search for files matching a glob pattern in a directory (non-recursive, top-level only).","parameters":{"type":"object","properties":{"path":{"type":"string","description":"Base directory to search in"},"exclude":{"type":"string","description":"Glob pattern for files to exclude"}},"required":["path"]}}}]}
